{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"An article in the Yale Alumni Magazine"},{"time":5240,"text":"told the story of Clyde Murphy,"},{"time":7840,"text":"a black man who was a member\nof the Class of 1970."},{"time":12960,"text":"Clyde was a success story."},{"time":16320,"text":"After Yale and a law degree from Columbia,"},{"time":20160,"text":"Clyde spent the next 30 years"},{"time":22400,"text":"as one of America's\ntop civil rights lawyers."},{"time":26280,"text":"He was also a great husband and father."},{"time":30080,"text":"But despite his success,"},{"time":32840,"text":"personally and professionally,"},{"time":36080,"text":"Clyde's story had a sad ending."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39440,"text":"In 2010,"},{"time":41720,"text":"at the age of 62,"},{"time":44640,"text":"Clyde died from a blood clot in his lung."},{"time":50120,"text":"Clyde's experience was not unique."},{"time":54720,"text":"Many of his black classmates from Yale"},{"time":57600,"text":"also died young."},{"time":60080,"text":"In fact, the magazine article indicated"},{"time":64319,"text":"that 41 years after graduation from Yale,"},{"time":68040,"text":"the black members of the Class of 1970"},{"time":71240,"text":"had a death rate\nthat was three times higher"},{"time":74520,"text":"than that of the average class member."},{"time":78680,"text":"It's stunning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81240,"text":"America has recently awakened"},{"time":84680,"text":"to a steady drumbeat"},{"time":86880,"text":"of unarmed black men\nbeing shot by the police."},{"time":91960,"text":"What is even a bigger story"},{"time":96560,"text":"is that every seven minutes,"},{"time":99680,"text":"a black person dies prematurely\nin the United States."},{"time":104440,"text":"That is over 200 black people"},{"time":108280,"text":"die every single day"},{"time":110440,"text":"who would not die if the health\nof blacks and whites were equal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118240,"text":"For the last 25 years,"},{"time":120920,"text":"I have been on a mission"},{"time":122880,"text":"to understand why does race"},{"time":125680,"text":"matter so profoundly for health."},{"time":129759,"text":"When I started my career,"},{"time":131560,"text":"many believed that it was simply\nabout racial differences"},{"time":135960,"text":"in income and education."},{"time":138480,"text":"I discovered that while\neconomic status matters for health,"},{"time":144200,"text":"there is more to the story."},{"time":146120,"text":"So for example, if we look\nat life expectancy at age 25,"},{"time":151960,"text":"at age 25 there's a five-year gap\nbetween blacks and whites."},{"time":157080,"text":"And the gap by education\nfor both whites and blacks"},{"time":161040,"text":"is even larger than the racial gap."},{"time":164960,"text":"At the same time,\nat every level of education,"},{"time":169600,"text":"whites live longer than blacks."},{"time":172560,"text":"So whites who are high school dropouts"},{"time":174880,"text":"live 3.4 years longer\nthan their black counterparts,"},{"time":178600,"text":"and the gap is even larger"},{"time":181520,"text":"among college graduates."},{"time":184200,"text":"Most surprising of all,"},{"time":187240,"text":"whites who have graduated from high school"},{"time":190640,"text":"live longer than blacks\nwith a college degree"},{"time":194360,"text":"or more education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196600,"text":"So why does race matter\nso profoundly for health?"},{"time":200520,"text":"What else is it\nbeyond education and income"},{"time":205400,"text":"that might matter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":208040,"text":"In the early 1990s,"},{"time":210520,"text":"I was asked to review a new book"},{"time":213600,"text":"on the health of black America."},{"time":216200,"text":"I was struck that almost every single one"},{"time":219320,"text":"of its 25 chapters"},{"time":221600,"text":"said that racism"},{"time":223400,"text":"was a factor that was hurting\nthe health of blacks."},{"time":227360,"text":"All of these researchers"},{"time":230120,"text":"were stating that racism was a factor\nadversely impacting blacks,"},{"time":236080,"text":"but they provided no evidence."},{"time":238560,"text":"For me, that was not good enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241960,"text":"A few months later,"},{"time":243640,"text":"I was speaking at a conference\nin Washington, DC,"},{"time":246600,"text":"and I said that one\nof the priorities for research"},{"time":249800,"text":"was to document the ways\nin which racism affected health."},{"time":254880,"text":"A white gentleman stood in the audience"},{"time":257440,"text":"and said that while he agreed\nwith me that racism was important,"},{"time":262240,"text":"we could never measure racism."},{"time":264880,"text":"\"We measure self-esteem,\" I said."},{"time":268200,"text":"\"There's no reason"},{"time":269640,"text":"why we can't measure racism\nif we put our minds to it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":273720,"text":"And so I put my mind to it"},{"time":276240,"text":"and developed three scales."},{"time":278440,"text":"The first one captured\nmajor experiences of discrimination,"},{"time":282440,"text":"like being unfairly fired\nor being unfairly stopped by the police."},{"time":286720,"text":"But discrimination also occurs\nin more minor and subtle experiences,"},{"time":292040,"text":"and so my second scale,\ncalled the Everyday Discrimination Scale,"},{"time":296000,"text":"captures nine items"},{"time":297760,"text":"that captures experiences"},{"time":299120,"text":"like you're treated\nwith less courtesy than others,"},{"time":302440,"text":"you receive poorer service\nthan others in restaurants or stores,"},{"time":306040,"text":"or people act as if they're afraid of you."},{"time":309240,"text":"This scale captures"},{"time":312080,"text":"ways in which the dignity and the respect"},{"time":315680,"text":"of people who society does not value"},{"time":318640,"text":"is chipped away on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321960,"text":"Research has found"},{"time":325440,"text":"that higher levels of discrimination"},{"time":328320,"text":"are associated with an elevated risk\nof a broad range of diseases"},{"time":333880,"text":"from blood pressure to abdominal obesity"},{"time":337160,"text":"to breast cancer to heart disease"},{"time":339840,"text":"and even premature mortality."},{"time":343520,"text":"Strikingly, some of the effects\nare observed at a very young age."},{"time":348640,"text":"For example, a study of black teens"},{"time":354120,"text":"found that those who reported higher\nlevels of discrimination as teenagers"},{"time":361120,"text":"had higher levels of stress hormones,"},{"time":365520,"text":"of blood pressure"},{"time":367480,"text":"and of weight at age 20."},{"time":372440,"text":"However,"},{"time":375920,"text":"the stress of discrimination"},{"time":378480,"text":"is only one aspect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380440,"text":"Discrimination and racism"},{"time":382960,"text":"also matters in other\nprofound ways for health."},{"time":387280,"text":"For example, there's\ndiscrimination in medical care."},{"time":391080,"text":"In 1999, the National Academy of Medicine"},{"time":395400,"text":"asked me to serve on a committee"},{"time":397360,"text":"that found, concluded\nbased on the scientific evidence,"},{"time":402440,"text":"that blacks and other minorities"},{"time":404960,"text":"receive poorer quality care than whites."},{"time":408480,"text":"This was true for all kinds\nof medical treatment,"},{"time":412360,"text":"from the most simple"},{"time":414720,"text":"to the most technologically sophisticated."},{"time":418800,"text":"One explanation for this pattern"},{"time":421840,"text":"was a phenomenon\nthat's called \"implicit bias\""},{"time":425800,"text":"or \"unconscious discrimination.\""},{"time":428120,"text":"Research for decades\nby social psychologists"},{"time":430960,"text":"indicates that if you hold\na negative stereotype"},{"time":434480,"text":"about a group in your subconscious mind"},{"time":437560,"text":"and you meet someone from that group,"},{"time":440280,"text":"you will discriminate against that person."},{"time":442600,"text":"You will treat them differently."},{"time":444280,"text":"It's an unconscious process.\nIt's an automatic process."},{"time":448920,"text":"It is a subtle process, but it's normal"},{"time":452120,"text":"and it occurs even among\nthe most well-intentioned individuals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459280,"text":"But the deeper that I delved"},{"time":462320,"text":"into the health impact of racism,"},{"time":465360,"text":"the more insidious the effects became."},{"time":469160,"text":"There is institutional discrimination,"},{"time":472600,"text":"which refers to discrimination"},{"time":475440,"text":"that exists in the processes\nof social institutions."},{"time":480400,"text":"Residential segregation by race,"},{"time":482760,"text":"which has led to blacks and whites living\nin very different neighborhood contexts,"},{"time":487760,"text":"is a classic example\nof institutional racism."},{"time":493120,"text":"One of America's best-kept secrets"},{"time":497080,"text":"is how residential segregation"},{"time":499280,"text":"is the secret source"},{"time":501640,"text":"that creates racial inequality\nin the United States."},{"time":506800,"text":"In America, where you live"},{"time":509760,"text":"determines your access to opportunities"},{"time":512919,"text":"in education, in employment,"},{"time":516240,"text":"in housing and even\nin access to medical care."},{"time":521640,"text":"One study of the 171 largest\ncities in the United States"},{"time":528080,"text":"concluded that there is not even one city"},{"time":531400,"text":"where whites live\nunder equal conditions to blacks,"},{"time":534760,"text":"and that the worst urban contexts\nin which whites reside"},{"time":538720,"text":"is considerably better than the average\ncontext of black communities."},{"time":543920,"text":"Another study found"},{"time":545640,"text":"that if you could eliminate statistically"},{"time":548680,"text":"residential segregation,"},{"time":550360,"text":"you would completely erase\nblack-white differences in income,"},{"time":554520,"text":"education and unemployment,"},{"time":557040,"text":"and reduce black-white differences\nin single motherhood"},{"time":560360,"text":"by two thirds,"},{"time":561600,"text":"all of that driven by segregation."},{"time":564960,"text":"I have also learned"},{"time":567040,"text":"how the negative stereotypes"},{"time":569840,"text":"and images of blacks in our culture"},{"time":572840,"text":"literally create and sustain"},{"time":575880,"text":"both institutional\nand individual discrimination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580640,"text":"A group of researchers\nhave put together a database"},{"time":584480,"text":"that contains the books,"},{"time":586720,"text":"magazines and articles"},{"time":589760,"text":"that an average college-educated\nAmerican would read over their lifetime."},{"time":594480,"text":"It allows us to look within this database"},{"time":597320,"text":"and see how Americans\nhave seen words paired together"},{"time":602680,"text":"as they grow up in their society."},{"time":605200,"text":"So when the word \"black\"\nappears in American culture,"},{"time":609200,"text":"what co-occurs with it?"},{"time":611280,"text":"\"Poor,\""},{"time":612720,"text":"\"violent,\""},{"time":613960,"text":"\"religious,\""},{"time":615320,"text":"\"lazy,\""},{"time":616560,"text":"\"cheerful,\""},{"time":617800,"text":"\"dangerous.\""},{"time":619560,"text":"When \"white\" occurs,"},{"time":621080,"text":"the frequently co-occurring words"},{"time":623360,"text":"are \"wealthy,\""},{"time":624720,"text":"\"progressive,\""},{"time":626000,"text":"\"conventional,\""},{"time":628120,"text":"\"stubborn,\""},{"time":629360,"text":"\"successful,\""},{"time":630600,"text":"\"educated.\""},{"time":632280,"text":"So when a police officer"},{"time":635600,"text":"overreacts when he sees\nan unarmed black male"},{"time":641240,"text":"and perceives him\nto be violent and dangerous,"},{"time":645960,"text":"we are not necessarily dealing\nwith an inherently bad cop."},{"time":651280,"text":"We may be simply viewing"},{"time":653840,"text":"a normal American"},{"time":655880,"text":"who is reflecting\nwhat he has been exposed to"},{"time":659680,"text":"as a result of being raised"},{"time":662120,"text":"in this society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664080,"text":"From my own experience,"},{"time":667840,"text":"I believe that your race"},{"time":670480,"text":"does not have to be\na determinant of your destiny."},{"time":674720,"text":"I migrated to the United States"},{"time":677280,"text":"from the Caribbean island of Saint Lucia"},{"time":680440,"text":"in the late 1970s"},{"time":682840,"text":"in pursuit of higher education,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and in the last 40 years,"},{"time":688400,"text":"I have done well."},{"time":690280,"text":"I have had a supportive family,"},{"time":692920,"text":"I have worked hard,"},{"time":695240,"text":"I have done well."},{"time":697120,"text":"But it took more for me to be successful."},{"time":700600,"text":"I received a minority fellowship\nfrom the University of Michigan."},{"time":705440,"text":"Yes. I am an affirmative action baby."},{"time":710560,"text":"Without affirmative action,"},{"time":713360,"text":"I would not be here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"But in the last 40 years,"},{"time":719560,"text":"black America has been\nless successful than I have."},{"time":724720,"text":"In 1978, black households\nin the United States"},{"time":730040,"text":"earned 59 cents for every dollar\nof income whites earned."},{"time":735040,"text":"In 2015,"},{"time":737320,"text":"black families still earn 59 cents"},{"time":742200,"text":"for every dollar of income\nthat white families receive,"},{"time":746040,"text":"and the racial gaps in wealth\nare even more stunning."},{"time":750600,"text":"For every dollar of wealth\nthat whites have,"},{"time":753880,"text":"black families have six pennies\nand Latinos have seven pennies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758800,"text":"The fact is,"},{"time":760280,"text":"racism"},{"time":762240,"text":"is producing a truly rigged system"},{"time":766600,"text":"that is systematically disadvantaging\nsome racial groups in the United States."},{"time":772880,"text":"To paraphrase Plato,"},{"time":775080,"text":"there is nothing so unfair"},{"time":778880,"text":"as the equal treatment of unequal people."},{"time":783520,"text":"And that's why I am committed"},{"time":786440,"text":"to working to dismantle racism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789960,"text":"I deeply appreciate the fact"},{"time":792440,"text":"that I am standing on the shoulders"},{"time":795720,"text":"of those who have sacrificed\neven their lives to open the doors"},{"time":800080,"text":"that I have walked through."},{"time":802280,"text":"I want to ensure\nthat those doors remain open"},{"time":806200,"text":"and that everyone\ncan walk through those doors."},{"time":812320,"text":"Robert Kennedy said,"},{"time":814680,"text":"\"Each time a man\" --\nor woman, I would add --"},{"time":818240,"text":"\"stands up for an ideal"},{"time":820360,"text":"or acts to improve the lot of others"},{"time":822960,"text":"or strikes out against injustice,"},{"time":825560,"text":"he sends forth a tiny ripple of hope,"},{"time":829120,"text":"and those ripples can build a current"},{"time":832240,"text":"that can sweep down the mightiest walls\nof oppression and resistance.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":838040,"text":"I am optimistic today"},{"time":840120,"text":"because all across America,"},{"time":842720,"text":"I have seen ripples of hope."},{"time":845720,"text":"The Boston Medical Center"},{"time":847640,"text":"has added lawyers to the medical team"},{"time":851160,"text":"so that physicians can improve\nthe health of their patients"},{"time":855240,"text":"because the lawyers are addressing\nthe nonmedical needs their patients have."},{"time":860480,"text":"Loma Linda University\nhas built a gateway college"},{"time":864320,"text":"in nearby San Bernardino"},{"time":866160,"text":"so that in addition\nto delivering medical care,"},{"time":869480,"text":"they can provide job skills"},{"time":872320,"text":"and job training"},{"time":874000,"text":"to a predominantly minority,\nlow-income community members"},{"time":878800,"text":"so that they will have the skills\nthey need to get a decent job."},{"time":884960,"text":"In Chapel Hill, North Carolina,"},{"time":887360,"text":"the Abecedarian Project has figured out"},{"time":891080,"text":"how to ensure that they have lowered\nthe risks for heart disease"},{"time":896400,"text":"for blacks in their mid-30s"},{"time":899480,"text":"by providing high-quality day care"},{"time":902520,"text":"from birth to age five."},{"time":905240,"text":"In after-school centers\nacross the United States,"},{"time":908560,"text":"Wintley Phipps and the US Dream Academy"},{"time":911240,"text":"is breaking the cycle of incarceration"},{"time":914040,"text":"by providing high-quality\nacademic enrichment and mentoring"},{"time":918480,"text":"to the children of prisoners"},{"time":921200,"text":"and children who have\nfallen behind in school."},{"time":924600,"text":"In Huntsville, Alabama,"},{"time":926320,"text":"Oakwood University,"},{"time":927760,"text":"a historically black institution,"},{"time":930120,"text":"is showing how we can improve\nthe health of black adults"},{"time":934440,"text":"by including a health evaluation"},{"time":937480,"text":"as a part of freshman orientation"},{"time":940640,"text":"and giving those students\nthe tools they need"},{"time":943640,"text":"to make healthy choices"},{"time":945320,"text":"and providing them annually\na health transcript"},{"time":948720,"text":"so they can monitor their progress."},{"time":951520,"text":"And in Atlanta, Georgia,"},{"time":953280,"text":"Purpose Built Communities has dismantled\nthe negative effects of segregation"},{"time":959240,"text":"by transforming a crime-ridden,"},{"time":961920,"text":"drug-infested public housing project"},{"time":964880,"text":"into an oasis of mixed-income housing,"},{"time":968600,"text":"of academic performance,"},{"time":970800,"text":"of great community wellness"},{"time":973680,"text":"and of full employment."},{"time":976160,"text":"And finally,"},{"time":977880,"text":"there is the Devine solution."},{"time":980680,"text":"Professor Patricia Devine"},{"time":984400,"text":"of the University of Wisconsin"},{"time":987000,"text":"has shown us how we can attack"},{"time":990720,"text":"our hidden biases head on"},{"time":993720,"text":"and effectively reduce them."},{"time":996680,"text":"Each one of us"},{"time":998480,"text":"can be a ripple of hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001200,"text":"This work will not always be easy,"},{"time":1004720,"text":"but former Supreme Court Justice\nThurgood Marshall"},{"time":1008680,"text":"has told us, \"We must dissent."},{"time":1011600,"text":"We must dissent from the indifference."},{"time":1014040,"text":"We must dissent from the apathy."},{"time":1016120,"text":"We must dissent from the hatred\nand from the mistrust."},{"time":1019600,"text":"We must dissent"},{"time":1021280,"text":"because America can do better,"},{"time":1024560,"text":"because America has no choice\nbut to do better.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}